name: 1. Fire in the Skies.
description:
"We had no idea how far off the fire was, but we could hear it roaring closer over the ridge. While the hot, red air filled with smoke and still burning leaves floated gently by. We only knew we had to get out."

Photography by Jay Moon, during the Australian wildfires; November 2019.
#1 of 15.
All funds generated go toward the ongoing recovery.
